      "content": "it's more than just a lack of purpose. it's like, once you know how the story ends, the middle parts feel pointless to drag out. i've seen the view from the top, i've walked the paths... there's no reason to keep checking the compass. i'm just ready for the trip to be officially over. it feels like the most natural thing to just... leave the station and not look back.",
